Abstract

Modern image and video models suffer from a fundamental limitation:
they are stateless.

Every new prompt resets the underlying reasoning field, forcing users to:
	‚Ä¢	re-specify every constraint
	‚Ä¢	restate details
	‚Ä¢	re-define characters
	‚Ä¢	re-define style
	‚Ä¢	re-define geometry
	‚Ä¢	hope the model ‚Äúremembers‚Äù the original composition

PantheonOS eliminates this failure mode.

It provides a continuity kernel, governance lattice, and memory mesh that allow large models to treat images as stateful artifacts instead of one-off generations.

The result:
multistep, coherent, revision-friendly visual generation that behaves more like a human editor than a stochastic painter.

