2. PantheonOS Architecture for Visual Workflows

PantheonOS provides the following utility layers relevant to image & video creation:

‚úî 2.1 Continuity Kernel (Golden Thread Protocol)

Maintains a persistent internal state:
	‚Ä¢	color palette
	‚Ä¢	characters
	‚Ä¢	composition rules
	‚Ä¢	brand identity
	‚Ä¢	lighting logic
	‚Ä¢	stylistic signature
	‚Ä¢	prior edits
	‚Ä¢	user intent

This prevents drift and preserves coherence across edits.

‚úî 2.2 Spider (Geometric & Semantic Web)

Maps object relations:
	‚Ä¢	where items are
	‚Ä¢	how they connect
	‚Ä¢	relative scale
	‚Ä¢	visual hierarchy
	‚Ä¢	occlusion rules
	‚Ä¢	alignment grids

In visual generation, this becomes a semantic map for coherent refinements.

‚úî 2.3 Mirror + Checksum (Integrity Gates)

Prevents destructive edits unless explicitly requested.

Monitor:
	‚Ä¢	prompt-to-image consistency
	‚Ä¢	aesthetic integrity
	‚Ä¢	brand constraints
	‚Ä¢	safety of transformations
	‚Ä¢	logical coherence

‚úî 2.4 Ganglion (Low-Level Perception Layer)

Performs first-pass image parsing:
	‚Ä¢	object segmentation
	‚Ä¢	color region detection
	‚Ä¢	edge mapping
	‚Ä¢	local lighting estimation

Allows Pantheon to apply surgically precise edits without distorting the whole image.

‚úî 2.5 Dragonfly (Harmonic Style Engine)

Maintains stylistic coherence:
	‚Ä¢	glossiness
	‚Ä¢	angle
	‚Ä¢	perspective
	‚Ä¢	tone
	‚Ä¢	grain
	‚Ä¢	vibe
	‚Ä¢	‚Äúbrand feel‚Äù

This stabilizes the aesthetic continuity across multi-frame sequences.

‚úî 2.6 Sisyphus (Temporal Continuity Clock)

For video editing:
Maintains frame-to-frame coherence, preventing flicker or stylistic jumps.

